        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): thread remote batch HTTP timeout budget",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Thread the configured remote embedding batch timeout through current memory-host SDK HTTP helpers and provider batch upload/create/status/error-read/download calls.\n- Use one shared remaining-time budget across submit, wait, error-read, retry, and download phases so the documented full batch timeout is not overspent.\n- Avoid replaying already accepted provider batches after HTTP aborts; surface timeout/fallback behavior without duplicate remote submissions.\n- Port the useful idea from #49981 with credit to @yintamaa while dropping stale unrelated churn.\n\n## Credit\nBased on the timeout threading work and investigation in https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/49981 by @yintamaa.\n\n## Validation\n- pnpm check:changed\n- Add focused regression coverage for SDK timeout forwarding and provider batch wait/download remaining-budget behavior.\n\nProjectClownfish replacement details:\n- Cluster: ghcrawl-156843-autonomous-smoke\n- Source PRs: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/49981\n- Credit: Credit @yintamaa and source PR https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/49981 for identifying and implementing the remote embedding batch timeoutMs threading approach.; Mention that the new PR is a fresh narrow port because the original branch is stale against the current memory-host SDK/provider-plugin layout and includes unrelated churn.; Keep #49937 and #49963 as historical context for the already-fixed direct/inline timeout issue, not as source PRs for this remote-batch HTTP fix.\n- Validation: pnpm check:changed\n",
